  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google offers a service called Find My Device that can help you locate your lost Android phone. However, this service primarily tracks the phone using your Google account and the phone's location services, not specifically by IMEI number.\n\nTo use Find My Device:\n1. Sign in to your Google account\n2. Go to find.google.com\n3. Select the lost device\n4. You can:\n- See its location\n- Ring the device\n- Secure the device\n- Erase the device if necessary\n\nWhile the IMEI number itself isn't used for tracking, it can be helpful for:\n- Reporting the phone as stolen to your carrier\n- Blocking the device on cellular networks\n- Insurance or police reports\n\nFor the best chance of finding your phone, make sure:\n- Location services are enabled\n- The phone is turned on\n- The phone has an internet connection\n- You're signed into your Google account on the device\n\nIf you haven't already, consider setting up Find My Device before losing your phone.",
